":"Call the implement-stage function with an artifact dict that contains a 'grounding' entry (LLM mocked). Assert that the function reads from the 'grounding' key and that the resulting/updated artifact dict contains a 'plan' entry whose value derives from the grounding input.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.68,"Integration":0.24,"System":0.02,"Agentic":0.04,"Workflow":0.02}},{"behavior_id":3,"description":"Deep-dive no longer overwrites 'plan' as a redundant side effect when diagnosis already exists in issue content.","minimum_level":"Unit","justification":"MOCK-MISS: The failure is a conditional inside deep-dive: 'if diagnosis already present, skip plan write'. This is entirely within one function's logic. Pass in an issue object with a pre-populated diagnosis field and assert no 'plan' artifact write occurs. No cross-module wiring is needed. REAL-INFRA: No. LLM-DEP: No — the condition is based on the presence of an existing diagnosis field, not LLM output quality.","test_description":"Call the deep-dive skill with an issue object that has a non-empty 'diagnosis' field. Assert that the artifact store's write method is never called with key='plan', confirming the redundant side effect has been removed.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.75,"Integration":0.18,"System":0.02,"Agentic":0.03,"Workflow":0.02}},{"behavior_id":4,"description":"In a full multi-step agent run (deep-dive → evaluate → implement), the final implementation plan reflects grounding produced earlier in the run.","minimum_level":"Workflow","justification":"MOCK-MISS: The failure only appears when artifact state produced in one step (evaluate writes 'grounding') must survive and be visible to a later step (implement reads 'grounding'). This crosses at least two stage boundaries in sequence. MULTI-STEP: The scenario is explicitly three sequential agent steps sharing state through an artifact store; the